The paper focuses on monitoring human physiological response during Human-Robot Collaborative (HRC) tasks, which involves both human and robot interaction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also discusses the importance of synchronization of data collected, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a data visualization tool for easy analysis of collected data, which could fall under the category of cs.CYBER (Cybernetics). The framework presented in the paper can also be applied to various HRC tasks, which could fall under the categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
